 BY SALIU SALIU THE Kaduna State Government has said some bandits have killed a father and his son in the Igabi Local Government Area of the state. Commissioner for Internal Security and Home Affairs, Samuel Aruwan, confirmed the incident in a statement on Sunday in Kaduna. Aruwan quoted security agencies who reported to the State Government that armed bandits invaded Baka village in Igabi Local Government Area on Saturday night. He said, the bandits, operating in groups, also abducted a number of persons, mostly women and children. “Troops based in the Sabon Birni general area were mobilised to the location,” he disclosed. According to him, the group engaged the bandits and rescued captives from one of the bandit camps. Governor Nasir el-Rufai has however expressed grief over the attack and condoled the family of the deceased The Governor prayed for the repose of their souls, while commending the troops for their quick response to the incident, including the rescue of 13 victims. 